To determine how long one notepad will last, we need to consider two factors: 
1) The number of days the notepad can be used before it runs out of paper.
2) The frequency at which notes are written on each day.

Let's assume that Harmony uses all five sheets of paper for each note she writes and doesn't reuse any part of a sheet. If someone wrote ten notes per day, they would use up one full notepad in 10 days (5 sheets/note * 1 notepad). 

However, if the person only used four sheets of paper per note or reused parts of the sheets, then the notepad could last longer than 10 days depending on how many notes are written each day. Without more information about the usage pattern, we can't determine an exact duration for one notepad to last with ten notes per day.
